channel.title: Windows 7 JDK
channel.description: Ok, I [u]had[/u] a laptop, that was windows XP, and I could download Java JDK just fine. But now I have a Windows 7 Desktop, and JDK won't download at all. I keep getting an error that says: Jdk-6u23-windows-x64.exe is not a valid win32 application. I've tried downloading about 4 different types of JDK, all do not work for my Windows 7. I've also searched google for answers, but none help. So tell me, wtf is going on here. (Oh yeah, forgot to mention that this is a 64-bit operating system).
